STEP 1 — I(1) PREREQUISITE CHECK  |  5-year data
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

For each series, run two ADF tests on log(price) with autolag='AIC':
  (a) Level test:      adfuller(log_price, autolag='AIC')
  (b) Difference test: adfuller(log_price.diff().dropna(), autolag='AIC')  [= log returns]

A series is I(1) if: level p > 0.05 (non-stationary) AND diff p < 0.05 (stationary returns).

Display as a compact banner:
  • Both I(1) → green success, show level and diff p-values for each ticker.
  • Level non-stationary but diff also non-stationary → amber warning (possibly I(2)); proceed anyway.
  • Level stationary (unusual) → amber warning; proceed anyway.


