REGRESSION VERSION REFERENCE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Four possible regression specifications (for reference):
  Version 1: OLS(price, price) no constant    → ADF on (A − β·B)
  Version 2: OLS(price, const+price)          → ADF on residuals
  Version 3: OLS(log, log) no constant        → ADF on (logA − β·logB)
  Version 4: OLS(log, const+log) ← CURRENT   → ADF on residuals

Version 4 is used throughout because: log-log gives β an economically meaningful elasticity
interpretation; the constant absorbs scale differences between tickers; adfuller on OLS
residuals with autolag='AIC' selects lag length automatically rather than defaulting to a
statsmodels heuristic.
